'''Yoshiwara Gion Festival''' (吉原祇園祭, Yoshiwara Gion-sai) is a festival held annually on the second Saturday and Sunday of June in the Yoshiwara district of [[:en:Fuji, Shizuoka|Fuji, Shizuoka]], formerly [[:en:Yoshiwara, Shizuoka|Yoshiwara City]], Shizuoka Prefecture.
== Overview == * One of the historically long-standing festivals originating during the time of Yoshiwara City. * Known locally as "Oten no San," it is called the foremost Gion Festival in the Tōkai region. * The primary venue, {{ill|Yoshiwara Shopping Street|ja|吉原商店街|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshiwara Shopping Street|qq=|1=Yoshiwara Shopping Street|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q133934514}}, stretches approximately 1 km with over 200 stalls lining the streets, attracting more than 200,000 visitors over two days. * Although named a [[:en:Gion Matsuri|Gion Festival]], it is not a direct continuation of Kyoto's Gion Festival. The style of the festival reflects influences from various local traditions, as Yoshiwara was a {{ill|Shukuba|lt=Shukuba|lt=Post town|ja|宿場町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/post town|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 宿場}}.
